I enjoy how consistently overboard this goes in terms of weirdness and continues to top itself with twists, yet still has momentum throughout and manages not to be boring and does manage to be incredibly entertaining. My one real complaint is that I never really could fully reconcile my thoughts on who Redd really is with tales that are exposition dumps on him (I think yes is the only one that really did it in a way I could get behind, but then this can't really be too compared to that). This manages to at least leave some element of mystery behind, so in that regard, this one still works.







