05 Jan 2016 17:10






I've already told you my general opinion personally but I'll put it here for the record: I really dig this. When things are built up for so long in the way the Misters are, with Redd as the big question mark, when you finally  it will usually turn out to be disappointing compared to the hype. So I was really pleasantly surprised with how good this was.

It maintains a fitting, semi-surreal atmosphere that really works great for the piece as a whole, and every connection made to other works feels wholly deserved. Connections to the Scarlet King are the kind of thing that makes me afterwards think , which is pretty much perfect for a reveal.

I could probably go on for longer about why I think this is great, but it'd just tend into rambling: I really really like this.







